title: Pilot
description: The story about the people from the fictitious Native settlement of Lynnx River begins when Eric Olssen moves from Vancouver to begin a new life after his marriage has failed and his partner has died. Eric tries to fit in with the residents, but he will find it hard to adapt to their customs.

title: A Different Drummer
description: Eric becomes involved in a fight between Leon Deela and his wife Rosie when Leon files charges. Eric also tries to put Albert Golo and his sons out of business.

title: The Road Not Taken
description: The residents of Lynx River have mixed feelings towards two government surveyors who announce their plans for a new highway through the town. Al Bishop returns and desperately tries to get along with Sarah.

title: Fair Trade
description: Teevee Tenia and Joey Small Boat find an old skeleton of a lost hunter and prepare to return it to the man's family. Albert Golo steals it and demands to get his family's bones out of a museum. RCMP Inspector Cormier comes to Lynnx River to see how is Eric doing.

title: Letting Go
description: Elsie Tsa Che draws attention to the obvious attraction between Eric and Sarah. Joey Small Boat and Teevee Tenia convince Hannah Kenidi to steal candies from Gerry's store. When Hannah's father comes Lynnx River, she sees the chance to dodge her troubled connection with Michelle.

title: Out of the Blue
description: U.S. Air Force pilots are forced to make a stop in Lynx River after a food poisoning emergency. While the captain is resting in the clinic, Eric is surprised to find Marie Tenia and Donna Kizha entertaining the others. Teevee fells guilty for the way his sister Marie was acting.

title: The Reunion
description: Eric's wife Lindy and two children come to Lynx River, but their reunion doesn't turn out the way they hoped, mostly because of Eric and Lindy's marriage difficulties. Michelle suspects a Wolverine Lake resident.

title: Birthright
description: Eric establishes a boxing program for local boys. Teevee isn't happy to see that Joey wants a relationship with his sister. Ellen refuses to give birth in Yellowknife. Harris Miller decides to establish a midwifery school.

title: Cold Comfort
description: Teevee wants to publish a videotape of Eric and Sarah in a compromising situation on cable television. Donna begins to act rebellious, which recovers Michelle's memories as a teenager.

title: The Act of Hares
description: Eric is frustrated by Sarah's recent strange behaviour. Andre LeBret attacks Peter because he thinks that Peter slept with his wife. Albert wants Eric to investigate Peter.

title: The Art of the Deal
description: Eric and Sarah try to convince Joe Gomba to stop eating meat because it hurts his stomach. Michelle suspects that Rico Nez, a new man in town, isn't working legally.

title: Sisters of Mercy
description: Eric's estranged son Andy comes to Lynx River and starts hanging out with Teevee--against his father's advice. Andy refuses to listen to his father and ends up in trouble. Hannah has difficulty at school.

title: Freeze Out
description: A night of drinking becomes a disaster for Leon Deela and his friend Ray Jhikhe when Ray dies. Leon blames Albert for Ray's death. An unknown person decides to resolve the issue by shooting Albert. Sarah is frustrated when Eric starts avoiding her. Rosie can't forgive Leon.

title: All About Leslie
description: A new student named Leslie attracts all the men in town, and both Teevee and Harris try to seduce her. But she only has eyes for Eric, and she will do anything to make him notice her. Rosie is driving everyone crazy with the wedding preparations.

title: Southern Comfort
description: Eric (who was meant to go to Hawaii on vacation, with Sarah) goes to Vancouver to find Teevee, who is trying to find Leslie. Teevee soon learns that Leslie has a boyfriend.And things get even worse.

title: Fire
description: Teevee has a fight with Michelle and becomes the prime suspect when her house burns down. To make room for Michelle and Hannah, Eric has to move into Sarah's apartment. He then has to decide whether to take the new job offer.

title: Bless This House
description: Sarah is unhappy when her father visits. Teevee is unimpressed by the new recreation center. Michelle is worried when Hannah doesn't seem to like the new house.

title: Ciao, Baby
description: Eric moves the rest of his things from Sarah's apartment. Bertha decides not to take the scholarship in Yellowknife. Peter interrupts Harris's deal with the Italians.

title: Miles to Go
description: Sarah is angry when she learns she can't go on vacation. Teevee is kicked out of school. Eric and Joe are looking for a missing hiker as they stumble upon a caribou.

title: Hostage
description: Andre LeBret takes hostages in the band office after Peter is unable to make a deal with the Italian furrier. Eric and Michelle are in charge of the situation, but things aren't going well for them.

title: Arrangements
description: Maria Sangali returns to Lynx River with new ideas--which don't go according to plan. Michelle isn't feeling well after the hostage situation. Sarah works with Albert.

title: Rumours
description: Inspector Cormier wants Michelle to accept a job out of town. Harris wants to marry Lois, but her brother doesn't support the marriage. Teevee advises Bertha to have an abortion. Sarah and Rosie argue while taking care of an injured Leon.

title: Lost Weekend
description: Peter brings an archaeologist to Lynx River who discovers something in town that might interest everyone. Sarah is down when she makes an incorrect diagnosis. Harris and Peter try to keep the tannery business afloat.

title: Raven
description: A convict returns to Lynx River, kidnaps Eric, and wants to take revenge on Michelle. Michelle hunts for him.

title: Maps and Dreams
description: Eric is frustrated when David Shore returns to Lynx River and spends time with Michelle. Gerry considers closing his business. In Edmonton, doctors must decide whether Sarah is ready to return to work.

title: Born Again
description: Sarah returns to Lynx River and her work. She does her best to regain the confidence of people she let down.

title: Crossing the River
description: Eric is still angry when he sees David with Michelle. Sarah moves in with Albert. Bertha decides to forget about Teevee and move on with her life. Peter tries to encourage Teevee to work and learn about responsibility.

title: Follow the Leader
description: Peter and Albert fight for control of the tannery. Peter talks to Michelle about her relationship with David. Eric is upset to find out that Sarah is living with Albert.

title: Trapped
description: Rosie wants to open a restaurant, but Eric wants to spend the money for other things. Two animal rights activists come to Lynx River protesting against the tannery.

title: All Fall Down
description: When the material for the tannery arrives damaged, Harris discovers that he didn't purchase an insurance policy on the company. Rosie talks to Gerry about opening a caf in town. David decides to end his relationship with Michelle.

title: Harvest
description: Rosie and others are depressed when the local tannery plans fail, but Peter has another plan. Gerry decides to raise prices to recuperate money he lost.

title: The Getting of Wisdom
description: Peter and Albert assume they are the primary candidates for the position of band chief in Lynx River-until a third candidate arrives. Eric's children come to visit again, with surprises.

title: Fallen Angel
description: Albert uses his new powers as chief for personal favours--with inevitable problems. Sarah discovers that some children are sniffing gasoline. Michelle worries that Hannah might be one of them.

title: The Long Goodbye
description: Everyone in Lynx River is shocked by Eric's sudden death. His wife Lindy comes to get his things. Albert considers replacing the RCMP detachment with a band constable.

title: Pulling Up Stakes
description: A diamond mining company is working near Lynx River, and the residents are unhappy about it. Michelle learns about Hannah's rebellious behaviour.

title: Partners
description: Bertha returns to Lynx River, and Teevee tries to make things right with her. Gerry's shop isn't profitable, and Rosie considers buying it.

title: The Cure
description: Albert convinces Betty not to create a new treatment center in Fort McIntyre. Betty comes to Lynx River with Sandy Carlisle. Peter wonders what made Betty change her mind. Bertha tries to tolerate Teevee's laziness.

title: A Rock and a Hard Place
Spin Dry
description: Michelle and Hannah's weekend camping brings ugly memories to Michelle of her childhood. Teevee tries to convince Bertha to stay in Lynx River. Betty has new plans for the treatment center.

title: You Can't Get There from Here
The Gift
description: Peter considers accepting a job offer from Ottawa. Bertha is frustrated because Teevee can't support her or the baby. Betty offers Sarah a job at the treatment center, but Albert isn't happy about it, so he asks Sandy to get Betty out of his way.

title: The Ties That Bind
description: Albert's old friend Ben Montour comes to Lynx River, wanting to get his life back on track, but Ben finds it difficult to cope with people in town. Ellen and Peter's relationship faces a crisis.

title: Break Dance
description: Michelle alerts Sarah about Albert, but Sarah doesn't believe her. Teevee is shocked when he finds a familiar face in Ben Montour's motel room.

title: Shelter
description: Albert is away from Lynx River, so Peter has an opportunity to become chief. Teevee isn't happy to see an old acquaintance from Vancouver. Leon and Rosie argue over her work responsibilities.

title: Life Is a Memory
description: Lois decides to take drastic measures after being rejected by both Ben and Harris. Rumours spread through town about Nevada being HIV positive, causing havoc.

title: Refugees
description: Sarah worries about her baby's future if Albert continues to disappear. Nathan wants to end his punishment. Gerry's house and Ben Montour's raven sculpture are in danger.

title: Arrival and Departure
description: Hannah returns to Lynx River, with some noticeable changes. Brian's wife comes to Lynx River, determined to stay for good.

title: Limbo
description: A frustrated Gerry closes his store. Sarah doesn't want to give birth in Yellowknife. Ellen is angry when Peter doesn't appear to care about their baby. Nathan's isolation exhibits signs of insanity.

title: The Visit
description: Michelle leaves for Calgary to visit Hannah. She learns that Hannah is missing and decides to find her with the help of Andrew One Sky. Teevee returns to Lynx River with a new girlfriend and a lot of money.

title: Take Me Home
description: Teevee learns that the mine where he has been working has been closed. He has no money to pay for the motel where he been staying with Anne-Marie, so they are forced to move in with his family. Sarah can't wait for her baby to come. Michelle, Louis, and Andrew continue to search for Hannah.

title: The Weight
description: Following the tragedy of Hannah's death, Michelle wants Inspector Cormier to transfer her to Yellowknife. Sarah isn't ready to face Michelle, but when she does, Michelle isn't likely to react the way Sarah hoped she would. Wayne is having more difficulty than he has ever had dealing with Hannah's death.

title: A Shot Rang Out
description: Freddy Small Boat, about to die in a few days, accuses Albert of murdering Rosie's father 27 years ago. Rosie wants Albert arrested, but there isn't enough evidence. As the investigation progresses, tension rises in Lynx River.

title: Revolving Door
description: Andrew One Sky, the psychologist who helped Michelle search for Hannah in Calgary, comes to Lynx River. Coincidentally, Ellen needs a counselor to help her keep the treatment center open. Teevee and Bertha continue to fight.

title: Traces and Tracks
description: Michelle arrests William for smuggling drugs, and he pesters her until she knocks him unconscious. Teevee applies for a new job. Sarah returns to Lynx River looking for a place to stay.

title: To Have and to Hold
description: Sarah continues to search for living quarters for herself and the baby. Harris and Lois prepare for their wedding, but everything goes wrong. Michelle and Andrew argue over the treatment center.

title: A Safe House
description: Peter expresses his frustration about Michelle's relationship with Andrew One Sky. Teevee receives bad news about his recent job application. Betty comes to Michelle's house with Suzie Muskrat's son Charlie.

title: Prodigal Son
description: A fire breaks out in the treatment center, and Ellen is worried about the insurance. Suzie Muskrat comes to Lynx River, looking for her son Charlie. Rosemary and Brian return from Vancouver, concealing the real reason why they left.

title: Bushman
description: Michelle wants to know what is happening with the treatment center, but Andrew warns her not to ask about it. Charlie has nightmares after seeing someone in the bushes.

title: Never Surrender
description: Albert stops helping Sarah raise her baby and files a complaint against her with social services. Elsie plans a birthday party for her daughter and suffers difficulties with her memory. Ellen returns for the party and talks to Peter about their relationship.

title: Partners and Other Strangers
description: Sylvie LeBret returns and revives ghosts of the past. Charlie starts using Michelle's hunting training to keep people from building a road on disputed land. Teevee and Gerry's sawmill arrives, and now Teevee must make the job work.

title: Fear of Flying
description: Peter makes Sarah a new job offer. Andrew takes a new job, which could keep him away from Michelle and Charlie for a long time.

title: Simple Sufferings
description: Teevee needs to work with Albert Golo while making a big order for the sawmill, but Elsie suspects that Teevee might be in danger. Rosie spends time with Gerry while Leon is away. Lois wants to be a minister, but she runs into obstacles.

title: Suspicious Minds
description: Michelle tries to find out why Brian is acting strangely. Bertha and Teevee get into an argument related to mill business. Elsie tries to stop Sylvie from becoming a schoolteacher in town.

title: A Deeper Silence
description: Leonard Sahke, a drug addict, comes to town, so Brian and Michelle are forced to ask William MacNeil for help. Michelle tries to find out both who stole her notebook and why Brian is behaving strangely.

title: Walking with Ghosts
description: Michelle continues her search for Brian with help from the RCMP rescue team. Betty Moses returns to re-open the treatment center and offer Sarah a job. Lois gives Harris news that upset him.

title: Hunting in the Dark
description: Michelle goes to Vancouver to search for both Brenda Shore and the answer to Brian's apparent suicide. Sarah's housewarming party reminds Albert of his and Sarah's troubled relationship.

title: The Higher Law
description: Michelle and the RCMP are puzzled when Albert's house burns down and Albert disappears. Inspector Cormier informs Michelle about a possible upgrade, with strings attached.

title: The Road
description: Plans for building a road in Lynx River are still in progress. Constable James Harper is surprised that Michelle isn't leaving the force. Sarah continues to have visions of Albert.

title: Cold
description: Brenda Shore returns expecting to be welcomed by Bertha and Teevee, but she may be surprised. After clearing the road, Teevee remains trapped in a blizzard with a friend.

title: Sleeping Dogs
description: Peter is hiding from a Revenue Canada agent. Nathan, James, and Joe are frustrated by Michelle's unwillingness to arrest Albert. Gerry's relationship with a bank officer goes into crisis.

title: Peter and the Wolf
description: Peter is stressed by an upcoming race. Leon receives an unexpected visitor. Sarah gets closer with a rig foreman.

title: The Smell of Violets
description: Constable James Harper and Inspector Cormier are still trying to determine who attacked Michelle and why Teevee is suddenly missing. Harris isn't happy about Jesse's upcoming christening, but Gerry is.

title: I Shall Not Want
description: Constable James Harper continues to investigate Michelle's shooting. Charlie is excited by Michelle's return, but he is also unhappy because she won't quit her job. Harris tries to find a way to help a desperate Lois.
